{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/algorithm/LEET/L1671MinimumNumberofRemovalstoMakeMountainArray/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"1671. Minimum Number of Removals to Make Mountain Array","date":"October 30, 2024"},"html":"<h1>문제 설명</h1>\n<p>이 문제는 주어진 배열이 mountain array가 되도록 만들기 위해 제거해야 하는 최소 숫자를 구하는 문제이다.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 103.50000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1671\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c927d0ada8a5f25692c578daba181011/5a190/1671.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c927d0ada8a5f25692c578daba181011/772e8/1671.png 200w,\n/static/c927d0ada8a5f25692c578daba181011/e17e5/1671.png 400w,\n/static/c927d0ada8a5f25692c578daba181011/5a190/1671.png 800w,\n/static/c927d0ada8a5f25692c578daba181011/3fca6/1671.png 1112w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>풀이 및 해설</h2>\n<p>이 문제를 풀기 위해서는 다음과 같은 방법을 사용할 수 있다.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>왼쪽에서 오른쪽으로 LIS를 구한다.</li>\n<li>오른쪽에서 왼쪽으로 LDS를 구한다.</li>\n<li>LIS[i] + LDS[i] - 1의 최대값을 찾는다.</li>\n<li>n - (LIS[i] + LDS[i] - 1)을 반환한다.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>풀이</h2>\n<pre><code class=\"language-python\">class Solution:\n    def minimumMountainRemovals(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        n = len(nums)\n\n        # calculate LIS from left to right\n        lis = [1]*n\n        for i in range(1,n):\n            for j in range(i):\n                if nums[i] > nums[j]:\n                    lis[i] = max(lis[i], lis[j]+1)\n        \n        # calculate LDS from right to left\n        lds = [1]*n\n        for i in range(n-2,-1,-1):\n            for j in range(n-1,i,-1):\n                if nums[i] > nums[j]:\n                    lds[i] = max(lds[i], lds[j]+1)\n        \n        # find max sum of LIS[i] + LDS[i] -1\n        max_length = 0\n        for i in range(n):\n            if lis[i] > 1 and lds[i] > 1:\n                max_length = max(max_length, lis[i]+lds[i]-1)\n        \n\n        # return the min num of removals\n        return n-max_length\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Complexity Analysis</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.50000000000001%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"tc\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d3d138d5a6286e28f776b22b47ac450f/5a190/tc.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d3d138d5a6286e28f776b22b47ac450f/772e8/tc.png 200w,\n/static/d3d138d5a6286e28f776b22b47ac450f/e17e5/tc.png 400w,\n/static/d3d138d5a6286e28f776b22b47ac450f/5a190/tc.png 800w,\n/static/d3d138d5a6286e28f776b22b47ac450f/f43e4/tc.png 1120w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3>시간 복잡도</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>O(n^2)의 시간이 걸린다.\n<ul>\n<li>LIS를 구하는데 O(n^2)의 시간이 걸린다.</li>\n<li>LDS를 구하는데 O(n^2)의 시간이 걸린다.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>공간 복잡도</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>O(n)의 공간이 필요하다.\n<ul>\n<li>LIS를 저장하는데 O(n)의 공간이 필요하다.</li>\n<li>LDS를 저장하는데 O(n)의 공간이 필요하다.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Constraint Analysis</h2>\n<pre><code>Constraints:\n3 &#x3C;= nums.length &#x3C;= 1000\n1 &#x3C;= nums[i] &#x3C;= 10^9\nIt is guaranteed that you can make a mountain array out of nums.\n</code></pre>\n<h1>References</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-number-of-removals-to-make-mountain-array/\">1671. Minimum Number of Removals to Make Mountain Array</a></li>\n</ul>"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/algorithm/LEET/L1671MinimumNumberofRemovalstoMakeMountainArray/"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}